column5: Well,  we picked a name for our boat... just had the letters made up last week. Looks okay, also had a couple of musky decals made up to cover up a big dent that was in the boat. I'm quite happy with how it turned out...   and the boat name!!!    Now we just need to get some more slime in it... the Musky kind lol
i'm planning to name my "girlfriend #2" ... if you do up a search here, there was a thread late last year/early this year started by ccmt
Searched and searched, thought and thought....several options made it to top five.....1) Big Kahuna, 2) Prime Rib, 3) Reef Slayer, and 4) The Next Filet......finally settled on "Alumacraft".
JB's Bay-bee.   When I get a boat worthy of a name
Hey Victor...  If you want the girlfriend to understand your priorities and her place in your life, might want to name the boat "girlfriend #1"
Mine is aptly named "Old Smokey"  due to my thirsty 89 Johnson LOL! Can't wait to put a new motor on her
well, i did put some thought into that. But i still want to live lol.

"The Tub" or as my girlfriend refers to it, "The Tub of War!"  She wanted a new bathroom and new bathtub, I wanted a bass boat.  I've thought about mounting a faucet on the cowling but am keeping under the radar or  Cheers
haha! I really like that one !
why would i tell you might steel her from me lol
WARCANOE  Aptly named by history and re-invented by my buddy RJ I think.
